    {
      "id": "UV2_xMd3hNzDyy-UQKkwu",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 742,
      "y": 154,
      "width": 935,
      "height": 425,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aF",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1683877243,
      "version": 876,
      "versionNonce": 822321845,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1784054324732,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "The @Service() decorator on a class:\n    - means you do not have to\n      create a \"provider\" manually for this.\n    - it will be created when you first inject it\n      and it will stay in memory as long as the application runs.\n\nUsing a provider (app.config.ts, the route, the component):\n    - Specifies the scope and lifetime of that service.\n        - Scope means \"who can see this instance\"\n        - Lifetime means \"when is it created?\"\n        - When does it go away?\n            - If you provide it on a component, it goes away after that component is \n              destroyed (you leave that page, etc.)\n        - You can say to destroy it when you leave a route.\n            - This is *big* - it means if you have a service that loads a LOT\n               of data, you can make it so it goes away when they are done with that\n               feature.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "The @Service() decorator on a class:\n    - means you do not have to\n      create a \"provider\" manually for this.\n    - it will be created when you first inject it\n      and it will stay in memory as long as the application runs.\n\nUsing a provider (app.config.ts, the route, the component):\n    - Specifies the scope and lifetime of that service.\n        - Scope means \"who can see this instance\"\n        - Lifetime means \"when is it created?\"\n        - When does it go away?\n            - If you provide it on a component, it goes away after that component is \n              destroyed (you leave that page, etc.)\n        - You can say to destroy it when you leave a route.\n            - This is *big* - it means if you have a service that loads a LOT\n               of data, you can make it so it goes away when they are done with that\n               feature.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "K8Z156oHfy-JswqweyXuX",
